cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a computer vision task related to image analysis and recognition. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a self-trained subspace learning paradigm, which involves solving an eigenvalue problem, indicating a machine learning approach. Thus, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple kernels to cope with non-linearity, which suggests a multimedia (cs.MM) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) aspect.
